Following is a table showing Indian companies plans
to sell shares through an initial public offering, or IPO, according to company
filings to the  Securities and Exchange Board of India .  At least 80 companies have pending  draft offer documents  with the regulator
seeking approval for share sales. Indian companies raised about 331 billion
rupees ($6.2 billion) from 52 IPOs in the year ended March 31. Since April, 28
companies have raised about 49 billion rupees.  Maiam Global Food Ltd. and Bluplast Industries Ltd. filed share sale
documents with the regulator last week.  
Source: The Securities and Exchange Board of  India , National Stock Exchange of
